AU  - Laffont, Jean-Jacques
AU  - Tirole, Jean
T1  - Adverse Selection and Renegotiation in Procurement
PY  - 1990
Y1  - 1990/10/01
DO  - 10.2307/2298088
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 57
IS  - 4
SP  - 597
EP  - 625
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - As was shown by Dewatripont, optimal long-term contracts under asymmetric information are generally not time-consistent. This paper fully characterizes the equilibrium of a two-period procurement model with commitment and renegotiation. It also analyzes whether renegotiated long-term contracts yield outcomes resembling those under either unrenegotiated long-term contracts or a sequence of short-term contracts, and links the analysis with the multiple unit durable good monopoly problem.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2298088
ER  - 



