T1  - Comparative Statics and Relative Convexity
PY  - 1990
Y1  - 1990/10/01
DO  - 10.2307/2298094
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 57
IS  - 4
SP  - 699
EP  - 706
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This paper shows that if the difference of two positive semidefinite matrices is positive semidefinite then the difference of their generalized inverses is negative semidefinite. It uses this to compare comparative static behaviour over feasible sets whose distance functions have Hessians with a positive semidefinite difference. It then interprets this condition in terms of various ideas of the relative convexity of the two sets and relates it to the Le Chatelier principle.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2298094
ER  - 



